The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, May 23: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has simplified the format of offer documents of mutual funds for the benefit of the investors. According to a Sebi circular, the offer documents would be split into three heads statement of additional information, scheme information document and key information memorandum.                            
	 Mumbai, May 23: The employees of the State Bank of India will hold a one-day nationwide strike on June 6 as a protest against the banks management policies on various issues including that of the pension scheme.                            
	 Mumbai, May 23: The Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) has warned that it would to take appropriate action including the suspension of trading in scrips if companies are found to be involved or acting in collusion with any person to defraud investors.                             
	 Paris, May 23: The head of the World Trade Organisation (WTO) Pascal Lamy said the conditions were at last favourable for a possible global trade agreement under the Doha round by the end of the year.                            
	 New Delhi, May 23: Videocon has said its talks to buy out the mobile handset business of the US-based Motorola are at initial stages and a deadline is yet to be fixed.
                                                                                                                               
